org.timepedia.chronoscope.client.plot
Class DefaultXYPlot

java.lang.Object
  org.timepedia.chronoscope.client.plot.DefaultXYPlot
All Implemented Interfaces:
XYDatasetListener, XYPlot, org.timepedia.exporter.client.Exportable
public class DefaultXYPlot
extends java.lang.Object
implements XYPlot, org.timepedia.exporter.client.Exportable, XYDatasetListener

A DefaultXYPlot is responsible for drawing the main chart area (excluding axes), mapping one or more datasets from (domain,range) space to (x,y) screen space by delegating to one or more ValueAxis implementations. Drawing for each dataset is delegated to Renderers. A plot also maintains state like the current selection and focus point.

Author:
Ray Cromwell <ray@timepedia.org>

getDomainStart

public double getDomainStart()
Description copied from interface: XYPlot
The minimum visible domain value over all datasets taking into account multiresolution representations. This value will differ from getDomainMin() if the zoomed out view of the Plot forces the renderer to user a coarser representation that may have different values. This can happen if dataset values in higher levels use interpolation rather than point sampling, for example.

Specified by:
getDomainStart in interface XYPlot
